Crime rate in Canada is much lower than in the States.  Following link is just an example to corroborate my claim:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.jointogether.org/gv/news/summaries/reader/0,2061,547013,00.html">www.jointogether.org/gv/n...13,00.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
So if your attempts at reducing crime ain't working, don't come crying on my shoulders.  Our system is pretty effective, and only reason why yours isn't is because you haven't taken the right approach.  Therefore, it is wise to invest more money into crime minimization because if it's 3 times higher than in Canada, there's lots of room for improvement.<br>
<br>
But then again, that's politics, and I didn't come here to start a policy dissertation, so I'll leave it at that. <br>
