<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Paying to support a criminals in jail is very relevant. Say we catch this sniper, he goes to jail , who do you think pays his bills? Its the tax payers who suffer in the long run.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yeah, but a big chunk of argument relied upon some criminals getting a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> free ride</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> by going to prison, and in this specific scenario, I doubt that is the case.  The killer is very intelligent, which in turn implies he's probably had to pay quite a sum for the training he acquired in order to elude the police for so long, and on top of that, he's moving around with a vehicle.  If he has a vehicle, chances are his real life would be of much better quality than his jail life.<br>
<br>
In all likeliness, if the perpetrator(s) is ever caught, he won't consider his apprehension as a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> free ride</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to jail, and thus why your reasoning is flawed since that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> free ride</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> statement doesn't pertain to this discussion.  <br>
<br>
In other words, it's not an acceptable premise, and if you've ever studied logic, you'd know that for a conclusion to be valid, all premises have to be acceptable, thus why I'm rejecting your conclusion.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I surely despise paying for any criminal to live.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Lot of things I despise in life, but I'd much prefer paying, knowing that the criminal will suffer as opposed to him receiving a quick and painless death.  It's a moral vs financial issue if I understand you correctly, and my morals prevail.<br>
<br>
But even then, ever thought of making those criminals somewhat compensate for the cost we incur by keeping them alive, like through manual labour maybe?  Community Service ring a bell?!? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111343">Nektar Nefaste</a><br>
